description.plain:
Maxwell Owusu Ansah, better known as Lethal Bizzle is an English rapper originating from Walthamstow.

His rise to fame came from his grime single with More Fire Crew; “Oi!”, which landed in the Top 10 UK Singles chart. His debut solo single “Pow (Forward)” charted at number 11 despite being banned from airplay and clubs for “causing too much mayhem”.

He released Against All Oddz in 2005 and Back to Bizznizz in 2007.

He is most renown for his singles rather than his albums including:


Pow 2011
Rari Workout
Fester Skank



The former of which are included on his compilation album Best of Bizzle.

In 2017, he released You’ll Never Make A Million From Grime EP, including the single with Skepta: I Win.

description.plain:
One of the hardest and most iconic grime tracks before seemingly the entire genre went mainstream, “Pow (Forward)” was also one of the most commercially successful despite being banned from the radio and seldom played at clubs due to the fact that it would inevitably lead to fights on the dancefloor.

Though credited to Lethal Bizzle, this song in fact consists of a selection of little-known rappers spitting short, extremely violent and patois-heavy verses, with Bizzle providing a hook of sorts and commentary at the beginning and end of the track.

A true grime classic.

description.plain:
After teasing the tune on his snapchat for a long time, Bizzle finally released his Xmas 2015 Charity Single on December 1st. Receiving attention for its unfestive and explicit content, it centres around classic Bizzle-esque themes, including working out (specifically in and on cars, with most of the video being filmed around his Lambourghini) and not-so-subtle sexual innuendos.

The song reached #49 in the UK iTunes Charts as an EP, which included accapella and instrumental versions of the song, as well as a clean radio edit (which mostly sounded the same as the instrumental).
